			<h3>About this article</h3>
			<span class="js-show"><a class="close-toolbox" href="#history-link-box"><img src="http://static.guim.co.uk/static/ee328ab8d8e6808034197b26fcd2d6eeb4d45d8e/common/images/close-popup.png" alt="Close this popup" title="Close this popup" /></a></span>
		</div>
		        	        			
						  			  		   		   	   	   
									
						
																	
 			<div class="section">
				<p><strong>David Simon: 'There are now  two Americas. My country is a horror show'</strong></p>
		   		    			    									   	This article appeared  on p30 of the <a href=http://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2013/dec/08/news  >Main section</a> section of 					   	<a href="http://www.theguardian.com/theobserver"  >the Observer</a>
					   	on <time datetime="2013-12-07" pubdate><a href="http://www.theguardian.com/theobserver/2013/dec/08">Saturday 7 December 2013</a></time>.
					   	It was published on
							<a href='http://www.theguardian.com/'>the Guardian website</a>
							at <time datetime="2013-12-07T19:00EST" pubdate>19.06 EST on Saturday 7 December 2013</time>.
					   	It was last modified at <time datetime="2014-07-18T09:55EDT">09.55 EDT on Friday 18 July 2014</time>.
						  				   								</div>
			</div>
</div>

